{"id": 5219, "title": "Ticket #5219: Memory leak in ClassAd function split()", "description": "<blockquote>\nThe <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ClassAd\" title=\"Class Ad\">ClassAd</a></span> function split() that's defined in the Condor utils lib allocates an <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ExprList\" title=\"Expr List\">ExprList</a></span> for the result of the function, which is then leaked. This is similar to the leak in splitUserName() and splitSlotName(), which was fixed in <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=3082\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('3082'); return false;\" title=\"memory leak in classad functions returing lists\">#3082</a></span>. The same fix should be used here.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2015-Aug-20 11:54:53 by johnkn:</em> <br/>\n\nCODE_REVIEW: change looks good. -tj</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Aug-27 12:43</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/ac769236bb2911137066dd557561bab6733cd2bf\">[45732]</a></span>: copy edited versions of 8.2.10 version history items into the 8.3.8 version history: <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5219\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5219'); return false;\" title=\"Memory leak in ClassAd function split()\">#5219</a></span> <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5234\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5234'); return false;\" title=\"condor_vacate ignores other arguments when -constraint is passed.\">#